Others: The Oklahoma City Thunder made a convincing 126-107 win over the Houston Rockets.
Shai Gilgeous-Alexander and Chet Holmgren combined for 58 points.
Six players finished with double-digit points, showcasing a strong offensive performance.
The Thunder had a season-low 16 forced turnovers.
The defense remained elite with a 97.3 defensive rating.
The Thunder will face the Golden State Warriors and Phoenix Suns in upcoming games.
